comment: The full subcategory generated by a subset of objects is the category with these objects and the same morphisms as the original. The result is always a subcategory (and it is full, meaning that all morphisms of the original category between objects in the subcategory is also in the subcategory), see definition 4.1(2) of [Adamek] p. 48. (Contributed by Mario Carneiro, 4-Jan-2017.)
